# Site Conventions

This is an Astro portfolio site. Follow these conventions when creating or editing content.

## File structure

```
src/
  data/
    site.ts         ← central config (name, URL, social links, motto, bio)
    entries.ts      ← directory listing of all work (case studies + side projects)
    writing.ts      ← external writing links
    bookmarks.ts    ← bookmarks and featured quote
  layouts/
    BaseLayout.astro      ← shell: meta tags, theme toggle, fonts, doodle tool
    CaseStudyLayout.astro ← case study wrapper: hero, tags, footer (extends BaseLayout)
  components/
    SiteHeader.astro ← fixed header with scroll-aware title reveal
    Directory.astro  ← three-column home listing (case studies / side projects / social)
    DoodleTool.astro ← opt-in doodle overlay (included by default via BaseLayout)
  styles/
    global.css      ← design tokens, type scale, spacing, dark mode, utilities
    case-study.css  ← all case study component styles (sections, stats, photos, grids)
  pages/
    index.astro     ← home page (uses Directory)
    contact.astro   ← contact page
    tag/[tag].astro ← tag index (auto-generated from entries.ts tags)
    *.astro         ← each case study or project is a standalone page file
```

## Adding a new case study

1. Create `src/pages/your-project.astro`
2. Use CaseStudyLayout with props: caseStudy, description, context, hero, tags
3. Structure content with these sections (in order):
   - Brief (`.brief-facts`, `.brief-role`)
   - Photos (`.cs-inline-photo` with `.photo-grid`)
   - Work sections (`.cs-section` with `.cs-h2`)
   - Outcomes (`.stat-row`, `.problem-points`)
4. Add an entry to `src/data/entries.ts` with the matching href
5. Tags use slug format: `{ label: 'design systems', slug: 'design-systems' }`

## Adding a side project

1. Create `src/pages/your-project.astro`
2. Use BaseLayout directly (not CaseStudyLayout)
3. Set `doodle={false}` and `caseStudy="project name"` on BaseLayout
4. Import `../styles/case-study.css` for shared component styles
5. Use `.content` wrapper instead of `.cs-wrap`
6. Include a `.cs-footer` with back link and `site.footer`
7. Add an entry to `src/data/entries.ts`

## Design tokens (from global.css)

Colors: `--paper`, `--ink`, `--spot`, `--muted`, `--border`, `--spot-bg`, `--ink-bg`
Fonts: `--font-pixel` (GeistPixelLine), `--font-body` (Libre Franklin), `--font-mono`
Spacing: `--sp-section` (64px) > `--sp-block` (48px) > `--sp-block-md` (32px) > `--sp-block-sm` (24px) > `--sp-element` (16px) > `--sp-snug` (12px) > `--sp-tight` (8px) > `--sp-micro` (4px)
Type scale: `--type-hero` (48px) > `--type-xl` (28px) > `--type-lg` (20px) > `--type-base` (14px) > `--type-sm` (12px) > `--type-xs` (10px)
Content width: `--content-max` (640px)

## CSS class patterns

- `.cs-wrap` -- max-width content container (case study pages)
- `.content` -- max-width content container (project/simple pages)
- `.cs-section` -- vertical padding block
- `.cs-h2` -- section heading (pixel font, --type-lg)
- `.cs-tag` -- tag pill
- `.stat-row` / `.stat` -- metric grid (default 3 columns, use `.stat-row--four` for 4)
- `.two-col` / `.col` -- side-by-side layout
- `.problem-points` / `.problem-point` -- stacked outcome items (add `.problem-point--divided` for borders)
- `.photo` / `.photo-grid` -- image figures (default 3:2 crop, use `.photo--native` to skip)
- `.brief-role` / `.role-list` -- role/shipped metadata
- `.project-links` / `.project-link-item` -- external link list
- `.inline-link` -- inline text link (spot color)
- `.body-text` -- standard paragraph
- `.callout` -- pixel font accent text

## Naming and tone

- All lowercase. Page titles, headers, section labels, navigation text.
- No periods in headings or labels.
- Pixel font (GeistPixelLine) for headings, labels, tags, navigation, and the header name.
- Body font (Libre Franklin, weight 300) for paragraph text.
- Direct, conversational tone. No filler words or marketing language.
- Use the slop-scrub-humanizer skill when writing any prose content.

## Config-driven values

All personal info lives in `src/data/site.ts`. Components import from there.
Never hardcode names, URLs, or social links in layout or component files.

## Static output

The site builds as static HTML. No server adapter, no SSR, no middleware.
Use `getStaticPaths()` for any dynamic routes (e.g., tag pages).
